name.text: Solve the inequality of the form p < b-ax

questiontext.text:
Solve \({@ee@} \leq {@bb-aa*x@} < {@dd@}\), as a subset of the real numbers represented by inequalities.
Also write this inequalities as interval of the real numbers.


(a) Give your answer as inequalities for \(x\).

Note: To enter inequalities, you should write the relevant symbols in the table below.

Inequalities symbol Input Syntax
\( \geq \) >=
\( \leq \) <=
\( <\) <
\( >\) >
\( a < x < b \) a < x and x < b
\( x > a\) or \(x < b \) a < x or x < b

[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]

[[feedback:prt1]]


(b) Give your answer as interval in the simplified form.

Note: To enter intervals of you real line, you should write the relevant text in the table below.

Intervals Input Syntax
\( [a,b] \) cc(a,b)
\( (a,b) \) oo(a,b)
\( [a,b) \) co(a,b)
\( (a,b] \) oc(a,b)
\( (a, \infty) \) oo(a,inf)
\( (-\infty, b] \) oc(-inf,b)
\( (-\infty, \infty) \) oo(-inf,inf)

[[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]

[[feedback:prt2]]

generalfeedback.text:
Worked Solution

(a) We want to solve \({@ee@} \leq {@bb-aa*x@} < {@dd@}\)
Separating both sides of the inequality, we have that,

\((1) : {@ee@} \leq {@bb-aa*x@}\)

\((2) : {@bb-aa*x@} < {@dd@}\)

First, we solve the direction \({@ee@} \leq {@bb-aa*x@}\)

\(\begin{align*} {@ee@} \leq {@bb-aa*x@} &\implies {@aa*x@} \leq {@bb-ee@} \\ & \implies x \leq \textstyle {@(bb-ee)/aa@} \\ & \implies x \in \textstyle {@oc(-inf, ((bb-ee)/aa))@} \end{align*}\)

Next, we solve the direction \({@bb-aa*x@} < {@dd@}\)

\(\begin{align*} {@bb-aa*x@} < {@dd@} & \implies {@-aa*x@} < {@dd-bb@} \\ & \implies {@aa*x@} > {@-dd+bb@} \\ & \implies x > \textstyle {@(-dd+bb)/aa@} \\ & \implies x \in \textstyle {@oo(((-dd+bb)/aa), inf)@} \end{align*}\)

Hence, the solution of the inequality is given by,

{@ta@}


(b) Representing these inequalities as an interval of the real line, we have,

\(\begin{align*} \{x \in \mathbb{R} : \textstyle {@ta@} \} &= \textstyle {@int_3@} \\ &= \textstyle {@int_4@} \end{align*}\)

prtcorrect.text: Correct answer, well done.

prtpartiallycorrect.text: Your answer is partially correct.

prtincorrect.text: Incorrect answer.

Worked Solution:

\({@cc@} \leq {@bb-aa*x@} < {@dd@}\)

We solve both inequalities separately:

\({@cc@} \leq {@bb-aa*x@}\)

\({@cc-bb@} \leq {@-aa*x@}\)

\({@(bb-cc)/aa@} \geq x\)

and,

\({@bb-aa*x@} < {@dd@}\)

\({@-aa*x@} < {@dd-bb@}\)

\(x > {@(bb-dd)/aa@}\).

Therefore, the answer to this inequality is the interval \({@(bb-dd)/aa@} < x \leq {@(bb-cc)/aa@}\), which is entered as \(x >{@(bb-dd)/aa@}\) and \(x\leq {@(bb-cc)/aa@}\).
